<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" ?>
<Defs>

  <ScenarioDef>
    <defName>40k_ImperialDomination</defName>
    <label>40K - Imperial Domination</label>
		<description>Your group is a collection of extraordinary individuals that volunteered to try and take over a planet. You start with quite a lot of technology and resources to help your mission.

		The Imperial institutions will have your back if you fulfill their demands.
		
		</description>
    <scenario>
		<name>Imperial Domination</name>
		<summary>An Imperial expedition of 6 citizens to an Imperial Frontier World.</summary>
		<playerFaction>			
			<def>PlayerFaction</def>
			<factionDef>IoM_PlayerFaction</factionDef>
		</playerFaction>
		<parts>
			<li Class="ScenPart_ConfigPage_ConfigureStartingPawns">
				<def>ConfigPage_ConfigureStartingPawns</def>
				<pawnCount>6</pawnCount>
			</li>
			<li Class="ScenPart_PlayerPawnsArriveMethod">
				<def>PlayerPawnsArriveMethod</def>
				<method>DropPods</method>
			</li>
			<li Class="ScenPart_StartingThing_Defined">
				<def>StartingThing_Defined</def>
				<thingDef>Silver</thingDef>
				<count>500</count>
			</li>
			<li Class="ScenPart_StartingThing_Defined">
				<def>StartingThing_Defined</def>
				<thingDef>MealSurvivalPack</thingDef>
				<count>75</count>
			</li>
			<li Class="ScenPart_StartingThing_Defined">
				<def>StartingThing_Defined</def>
				<thingDef>Readables_Cicero</thingDef>
				<count>1</count>
			</li>
			<li Class="ScenPart_StartingThing_Defined">
				<def>StartingThing_Defined</def>
				<thingDef>Steel</thingDef>
				<count>700</count>
			</li>
			<li Class="ScenPart_StartingThing_Defined">
				<def>StartingThing_Defined</def>
				<thingDef>Medicine</thingDef>
				<count>24</count>
			</li>
			<li Class="ScenPart_StartingThing_Defined">
				<def>StartingThing_Defined</def>
				<thingDef>Component</thingDef>
				<count>30</count>
			</li>
			<li Class="ScenPart_StartingThing_Defined">
				<def>StartingThing_Defined</def>
				<thingDef>Effigy_Emperor</thingDef>
				<stuff>WoodLog</stuff>
			</li>
			<li Class="ScenPart_StartingThing_Defined">
				<def>StartingThing_Defined</def>
				<thingDef>EcclesiarchyIcon</thingDef>
				<stuff>WoodLog</stuff>
			</li>
			<li Class="ScenPart_StartingThing_Defined">
				<def>StartingThing_Defined</def>
				<thingDef>Gun_StandardLasgun</thingDef>
				<count>2</count>
			</li>
			<li Class="ScenPart_StartingAnimal">
				<def>StartingAnimal</def>
				<count>1</count>
				<bondToRandomPlayerPawnChance>1</bondToRandomPlayerPawnChance>
			</li>
			<li Class="ScenPart_GameStartDialog">
				<def>GameStartDialog</def>
				<text>
Detaching from your mothership your dropship breaks through the atmosphere and the five of you can finally take a personal look at the frontiert world you've been assigned to explore and potentially bring under Imperial Law.


This is a game with 40k Corruption enabled.

Your pawns have a new need (Purity of Soul). Acts of worship and certain events may impact a pawns purity and lead tthem to fall to chaos.

To get information about a pawns soul, click on the alignment icon in the Pawn inspection tab.

The Imperium won't intervene in planetary matters as long as the wider stability isn't under threat. To contact Imperial authorities you need an advanced communications console. Only then may you gain access to advanced technology and Imperial support.

Beware of Xeno activities in the Sector. If unprepared an Invasion by non-human aggressors may well be the end of a planet.</text>
				<textKey>GameStartDialog</textKey>
				<closeSound>GameStartSting</closeSound>
			</li>
			<li Class="ScenPart_StartingThing_Defined">
				<def>StartingThing_Defined</def>
				<thingDef>IG_SynthAgent</thingDef>
				<count>50</count>
			</li>
			<li Class="ScenPart_StartingThing_Defined">
				<def>StartingThing_Defined</def>
				<thingDef>WoodLog</thingDef>
				<count>100</count>
			</li>
			<li Class="OHUShips.ScenPart_StartWithShip">
				<def>DropShip</def>
				<ShipDef>OHUDropShip</ShipDef>
			</li>
		</parts>
    </scenario>

	</ScenarioDef>  
	
	
	


	<ScenarioDef>
		<defName>40K_ChaosCult</defName>
		<label>Chaos Cult</label>
		<description>You are leading a small enclave of chaos cultists bent on taking over the planet for the gods of chaos. Difficult.</description>
		<scenario>		
		<name>Chaos Domination</name>
			<summary>Five cultists attempt to rebuild. Difficult.</summary>
			<playerFaction>
				<def>PlayerFaction</def>
				<factionDef>PlayerTribe</factionDef>
			</playerFaction>
			<parts>

				<!-- Config pages -->
				<li Class="ScenPart_ConfigPage_ConfigureStartingPawns">
					<def>ConfigPage_ConfigureStartingPawns</def>
					<pawnCount>5</pawnCount>
          <pawnChoiceCount>8</pawnChoiceCount>
				</li>

				<!-- Player starting stuff spawn method-->
				<li Class="ScenPart_PlayerPawnsArriveMethod">
					<def>PlayerPawnsArriveMethod</def>
					<method>Standing</method>
				</li>

				<!-- Player pawns modifiers -->
				<li Class="ScenPart_ForcedHediff">
					<def>ForcedHediff</def>
					<visible>false</visible>
					<context>PlayerStarter</context>
					<chance>0.5</chance>
					<hediff>Malnutrition</hediff>
					<severityRange>
						<min>0.2</min>
						<max>0.4</max>
					</severityRange>
				</li>
				<li Class="ScenPart_SetNeedLevel">
					<def>SetNeedLevel</def>
					<visible>false</visible>
					<context>PlayerStarter</context>
					<chance>1.0</chance>
					<need>Food</need>
					<levelRange>
						<min>0</min>
						<max>0.1</max>
					</levelRange>
				</li>

				<!-- Player starting things -->
				<li Class="ScenPart_StartingThing_Defined">
					<def>StartingThing_Defined</def>
					<thingDef>Silver</thingDef>
					<count>200</count>
				</li>
				<li Class="ScenPart_StartingThing_Defined">
					<def>StartingThing_Defined</def>
					<thingDef>Pemmican</thingDef>
					<count>300</count>
				</li>
				<li Class="ScenPart_StartingThing_Defined">
					<def>StartingThing_Defined</def>
					<thingDef>HerbalMedicine</thingDef>
					<count>20</count>
				</li>
				<li Class="ScenPart_StartingThing_Defined">
					<def>StartingThing_Defined</def>
					<thingDef>MeleeWeapon_Club</thingDef>
					<stuff>WoodLog</stuff>
				</li>
				<li Class="ScenPart_StartingThing_Defined">
					<def>StartingThing_Defined</def>
					<thingDef>MeleeWeapon_Spear</thingDef>
					<stuff>WoodLog</stuff>
				</li>
				<li Class="ScenPart_StartingThing_Defined">
					<def>StartingThing_Defined</def>
					<thingDef>MeleeWeapon_Knife</thingDef>
					<stuff>Jade</stuff>
				</li>
				<li Class="ScenPart_StartingThing_Defined">
					<def>StartingThing_Defined</def>
					<thingDef>Bow_Short</thingDef>
					<count>2</count>
				</li>
				<li Class="ScenPart_StartingThing_Defined">
					<def>StartingThing_Defined</def>
					<thingDef>Pila</thingDef>
				</li>
				<li Class="ScenPart_StartingAnimal">
					<def>StartingAnimal</def>
					<count>3</count>
					<bondToRandomPlayerPawnChance>1.0</bondToRandomPlayerPawnChance>
				</li>

				<!-- Scatter some things near player start -->
				<li Class="ScenPart_ScatterThingsNearPlayerStart">
					<def>ScatterThingsNearPlayerStart</def>
					<thingDef>WoodLog</thingDef>
					<count>500</count>
				</li>

				<!-- Game start dialog -->
				<li Class="ScenPart_GameStartDialog">
					<def>GameStartDialog</def>
					<text>The gods were very angry. The blood machines came at night. They swept through your village, cutting and burning your people with their blades and devil-fire.\n\nOnly a few of you escaped. Now, after a harrowing journey on foot, with no close friends to turn to, you must build a new home in the wilderness, like your ancestors did.</text>
					<closeSound>GameStartSting</closeSound>
				</li>

			</parts>
		</scenario>
	</ScenarioDef>
     

  
</Defs>